pageContext.claim: “Under the terms of this deal, South Korea will double the number of American cars that can enter the market each year. So the car companies are very happy with it, and it gets to be just much more fair.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump did a minor reworking of this earlier agreement, such as removing a few regulatory burdens for US automakers to export cars, but U.S. automakers were nowhere near the previous export cap.
